shared_text:
Village of Mundelein
April 15 at 6:31 PM ·

Mundelein and MHS to Host “Friday Night Lights” Initiative to Shine a Bright Light Throughout Community
To show the Mundelein community’s support of everyone impacted by the pandemic, the Village of Mundelein and Mundelein High School invite EVERYONE to participate in a "Friday Night Lights" event this Friday, April 17. Join us in this initiative by turning on your front porch lights from 8 to 9 pm and even posting items in your front window or on your door. Display signs, photos, MHS spirit wear or uniforms...anything to show your support of doctors, nurses, Village first responders, Village businesses and their owners, Mundelein High School classes, clubs or sports teams. We want to “light up Mundelein” to show our collective gratitude and community spirit. Please join us by turning on your porch lights this Friday night from 8 to 9 p.m. Thank you.

Today, the Governor announced the issuance of an extension of the “Stay-At-Home” order for the State of Illinois, as well as an extension of the mandatory school closure order. These will continue through April 30. As a result, Fremont School District 79’s physical schools and buildings will continue to be closed through April 30. We will have an anticipated reopen date of May 1. We will continue with our eLearning process during this time.

We will continue to keep families updated on a timely basis of any pertinent developments. Thank you.

post_text:
In our continuing commitment to provide the latest updates as it relates to the Coronavirus (COVID-19), Fremont School District 79’s physical schools and buildings will continue to be closed through April 7 due to the extension of the mandated school closure order issued by the Governor today. We will have an anticipated reopen date of April 8.

FSD79 still will be observing Spring Break from March 23 through March 27 before resuming eLearning activities on Monday, March 30.

Today’s announcement from the Governor also included a “Stay-At-Home” order for the State of Illinois, which will begin Saturday, March 21 at 5 p.m. and will continue through Tuesday, April 7. During this time, Illinois residents are still permitted to go to grocery stores, pharmacies, gas stations, go on walks, etc.

We will continue to keep families updated on a timely basis of any pertinent developments. Thank you.

Congratulations to Fremont Middle School student Animesh Bijawat who was recognized as the eighth-grade winner of the Ansel Brainerd Book Chapter of the Daughters of the American Revolution American History Month Awards.

This year is the 400th anniversary of the voyage of the Mayflower and the founding of Plymouth Colony. Animesh wrote an essay responding to the prompt: Imagine you were one of the passengers on the Mayflower; what would you have packed and why?

post_text:
#FSD79 has scheduled a lawn care application on the grounds of all schools on Monday, October 14, 2019 (students are not in attendance that date). The rain date for the application is October 19. All products will be applied by a licensed applicator/contractor and marked immediately following application.

If parents have any questions, please contact Daniel Wagner, Director of Buildings and Grounds at dwagner@fsd79.org.

post_text: The #FSD79 students in Mrs. DiMaggio and Mrs. Lesser's class had a blast performing text feature surgery. They had to diagnose different students based on their text feature needs.
